snippet.title: 2021 Solution Challenge Demo Day
snippet.description: Join us for the 2021 Solution Challenge Demo Day hosted by Google Developer Student Clubs. The top 10 finalist teams will demo their solutions live while judges pick the top 3 grand winners! With months in the making, these students have come together with their local Google Developer Student Club teammates at their universities to create some truly inspiring ideas to support the United Nations 17 Sustainable Development Goals.

snippet.title: Google Developer Student Clubs
snippet.description:
Google Developer Student Clubs are university based community groups for students interested in Google developer technologies. Students from all undergraduate or graduate programs with an interest in growing as a developer are welcome. By joining a GDSC, students grow their knowledge in a peer-to-peer learning environment and build solutions for local businesses and their community.

Learn more about GDSC →  http://goo.gle/gdsc

snippet.title: The latest from the TensorFlow channel
snippet.description:
TensorFlow Dev Summit 2018 - March 30, 2018
The Computer History Museum, Mountain View, CA 
Join us for the livestream (Keynote starts on March 30th 2018 at 9:30 AM PDT) ➔ https://goo.gl/EakyW1


Learn more here: https://www.tensorflow.org/dev-summit/
Follow TensorFlow on Twitter: https://twitter.com/tensorflow

TensorFlow Dev Summit brings together a diverse mix of machine learning users from around the world for a full day of highly technical talks, demos, and conversation with the TensorFlow team and community. At this point, we are unable to accept new applications, but welcome you to join our waiting list, in case a spot opens up for the in-person event. Please note that we will be livestreaming and recording all talks. They will be available on the TensorFlow Youtube channel & you can check the TensorFlow website and @tensorflow for updates.

snippet.title: Best Practices for Actions on Google
snippet.description:
Welcome to our series of videos that will bring you news & best practices about Actions on Google. Apps for the Google Assistant are the gateway for your users to engage with your services through Google Home, Android phones, iPhones, and in the future, through every experience where the Google Assistant is available. 
It’s a new, efficient way to interact with users and make them happy!

The goal of this series is to help developers be more productive and leverage this new platform. We will cover topics like: Voice UI, design and development of actions.

If you have any comments or suggestions, please let us know on twitter @actionsongoogle or at our G+ community https://g.co/actionsdev

The goal of this series is to help developers be more productive and leverage this new platform. We will cover topics like: Voice UI, design and development of actions.

If you have any comments or suggestions, please let us know on twitter @actionsongoogle or at our G+ community https://g.co/actionsdev

snippet.title: The Google Workspace Developer Show
snippet.description:
The Google Workspace Dev Show is made for developers interested in integrating with the Google Workspace APIs and developer tools. Episodes feature one or several Google Workspace and/or Google APIs or API features and generally feature a snippet of working code to help get you started. Open your apps to a larger world of users by backing up your app’s data to Google Drive, send notifications to their Gmail accounts, add events to their Google Calendars, push data into Google Sheets, auto-generate Google Slides presentations, or build add-ons with Google Apps Scripts. These are some of the technologies you’ll learn how to integrate on the Google Workspace Dev Show, hosted by Google engineer Wesley Chun!

Subscribe to Google Developers → https://goo.gle/developers

snippet.title: Launchpad Online
snippet.description: The Launchpad Online video series is for startups, hobbyists, and enterprise developers who want to integrate Google technologies into the web and mobile apps *they're* building. Each episode introduces a specific Google API, developer tool, or API feature, generally with a snippet of working code which viewers can take and drop into something they're working on. No need to reinvent the wheel here... take advantage of the APIs that Google has worked hard to build and made available to help *you* build that awesome app!

snippet.title: Google at the Game Developers Conference (GDC) 2014
snippet.description: The Google Developer Day at GDC 2014 on 18 March was our biggest yet. We made several announcements including game gifts, multiplayer invites, multiplayer support for iOS and Play Game statistics, content experiments for apps in Google Tag Manager, and more. On the advertising side we introduced Google Analytics in AdMob, in-app purchase ads and ad network optimization to boost your mediation revenue. Check out all the talks, demos and code examples from our engineers, developer advocates and product managers.
